    "description": "Whenever one of mpi processes dies the others are left hanging e.g. stalling whole testsuite. This can be circumvented by calling `MPI_Abort` in `excepthook`. \r\n\r\nI moved `traceback_writer_hook` from `yt/funcs.py` since it wasn't used anywhere besides `parallel_analysis_interface` and I had to call `MPI` directly.\r\n\r\nUPDATES:\r\n\r\n * moved except hooks to module level",
